  "body": "The network info on the primary site nav is useful but doesn't provide much context or any interaction:\r\n\r\n![Image 2021-02-03 at 3 51 00 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8097623/106824648-1e733300-6638-11eb-8adc-71b56c42dbd8.jpg)\r\n\r\n![Image 2021-02-03 at 3 51 34 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8097623/106824642-1b784280-6638-11eb-91a6-21d9b8dd8c78.jpg)\r\n\r\nI was expecting this to be a button toggle to choose the network (Pyrmont testnet? Others?). \r\n\r\nI propose we add some interaction here that provides more context - e.g. a tooltip on hover that explains \"this is the launchpad for [xyz] network\" or perhaps provide a dropdown of links where people can easily navigate back & forth between mainnet/testnet apps. Given what funds are at stake here (pun intended), I think in general we should push folks to go through a \"dry run\" on the Pyrmont testnet in order to get a practice round of the setup.",
